<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Info.plist ADDITIONS merged into the generated bundle Info.plist by Tauri
  (tauri.macos.conf.json `bundle.macOS.infoPlist`). Tauri deep-merges these keys onto the
  Info.plist it generates from the config (product name, version, CFBundleDocumentTypes from
  `fileAssociations`, LSMinimumSystemVersion from `minimumSystemVersion`, …), so this file carries
  ONLY the keys Tauri does not already emit.

  NSMicrophoneUsageDescription is the purpose string macOS shows in the microphone consent (TCC)
  prompt the first time Recording Guard opens an input stream. It is REQUIRED for mic access on
  macOS 10.14+ regardless of signing state — an app that opens a `cpal` input stream without it is
  killed by the OS with a TCC violation. This benefits even the current unsigned build.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
  <string>ANVIL uses the microphone only for the Recording Guard pre-flight check — a live level meter, noise-floor reading, and clap-test room-echo estimate. The audio is analysed live and is never recorded, saved, or sent anywhere.</string>
</dict>
</plist>
